#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:2
msgid "v2.0 Roadmap"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:6
msgid ""
"We're seeking `sponsors and supporters for urllib3 v2.0 on Open Collective "
"<https://github.com/sponsors/urllib3>`_. There's a lot of work to be done "
"for our small team and we want to make sure development can get completed on-"
"time while also fairly compensating contributors for the additional effort "
"required for a large release like ``v2.0``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:11
msgid ""
"Additional information available within the :doc:`sponsors` section of our "
"documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:15
msgid "**🚀 Functional API Compatibility**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:17
msgid ""
"We're maintaining **99% functional API compatibility** to make the migration "
"an easy choice for most users. Migration from v1.x to v2.x should be the "
"simplest major version upgrade you've ever completed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:21
msgid ""
"Most changes are either to default configurations, supported Python "
"versions, and internal implementation details. So unless you're in a "
"specific situation you should notice no changes! 🎉"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:27
msgid "v1.26.x Security and Bug Fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:29
msgid ""
"Thanks to support from `Tidelift <https://tidelift.com/subscription/pkg/pypi-"
"urllib3>`_ we're able to continue supporting v1.26.x releases with both "
"security and bug fixes for the forseeable future 💖"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:33
msgid ""
"If your organization relies on urllib3 and is interested in continuing "
"support you can learn more about the `Tidelift Subscription for Enterprise "
"<https://tidelift.com/subscription/pkg/pypi-urllib3?utm_source=pypi-"
"urllib3&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=docs>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:38
msgid "**🔐 Modern Security by Default**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:41
msgid "HTTPS requires TLS 1.2+"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:43
msgid ""
"Greater than 95% of websites support TLS 1.2 or above. At this point we're "
"comfortable switching the default minimum TLS version to be 1.2 to ensure "
"high security for users without breaking services."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:48
msgid ""
"Dropping TLS 1.0 and 1.1 by default means you won't be vulnerable to TLS "
"downgrade attacks if a vulnerability in TLS 1.0 or 1.1 were discovered in "
"the future. Extra security for free! By dropping TLS 1.0 and TLS 1.1 we also "
"tighten the list of ciphers we need to support to ensure high security for "
"data traveling over the wire."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:56
msgid ""
"If you still need to use TLS 1.0 or 1.1 in your application you can still "
"upgrade to v2.0, you'll only need to set ``ssl_version`` to the proper "
"values to continue using legacy TLS versions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:63
msgid "Stop Verifying CommonName in Certificates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:65
msgid ""
"Dropping support the long deprecated ``commonName`` field on certificates in "
"favor of only verifying ``subjectAltName`` to put us in line with browsers "
"and other HTTP client libraries and to improve security for our users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:72
msgid "Certificate Verification via SSLContext"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:74
msgid ""
"By default certificate verification is handled by urllib3 to support legacy "
"Python versions, but now we can rely on Python's certificate verification "
"instead! This should result in a speedup for verifying certificates and "
"means that any improvements made to certificate verification in Python or "
"OpenSSL will be immediately available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:84
msgid "**✨ Optimized for Python 3.7+**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:86
msgid ""
"In v2.0 we'll be specifically be targeting CPython 3.7+ and PyPy 7.3.10+ "
"(compatible with CPython 3.8) and dropping support Python versions 2.7 and "
"3.6."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:90
msgid ""
"By dropping end-of-life Python versions we're able to optimize the codebase "
"for Python 3.7+ by using new features to improve performance and reduce the "
"amount of code that needs to be executed in order to support legacy versions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:97
msgid "**🔮 Tracing**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:99
msgid ""
"Currently with urllib3 it's tough to get low-level insights into what how "
"your HTTP client is performing and what your connection information looks "
"like. In v2.0 we'll be adding tracing and telemetry information to HTTP "
"response objects including:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:104
msgid "Connection ID"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:105
msgid "IP Address resolved by DNS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:106
msgid "Request Method, Target, and Headers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:107
msgid "TLS Version and Cipher"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:108
msgid "Certificate Fingerprint, subjectAltName, and Validity Information"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:109
msgid "Timings for DNS, Request Data, First Byte in Response"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:113
msgid "**📜 Type-Hinted APIs**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:115
msgid ""
"You'll finally be able to run Mypy or other type-checkers on code using "
"urllib3. This also means that for IDEs that support type hints you'll "
"receive better suggestions from auto-complete. No more confusing with "
"``**kwargs``!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:120
msgid ""
"We'll also add API interfaces to ensure that when you're sub-classing an "
"interface you're only using supported public APIs to ensure compatibility "
"and minimize breakages down the road."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:127
msgid "**🎁 ...and many more features!**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:129
msgid "Top-level ``urllib3.request()`` API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:130
msgid "Streaming ``multipart/form-encoded`` Request Data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:131
msgid "More Powerful and Configurable Retry Logic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:133
msgid ""
"If there's a feature you don't see here but would like to see in urllib3 "
"v2.0, there's an open GitHub issue for making feature suggestions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:139
msgid "**📅 Release and Migration Schedule**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:141
msgid ""
"We're aiming for all ``v2.x`` features to be released in **mid-to-late "
"2021**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:143
msgid ""
"Here's what the release and migration schedule will look like leading up to "
"v2.0 being released:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:146
msgid "Development of ``v2.x`` breaking changes starts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:147
msgid ""
"Release ``v1.26.0`` with deprecation warnings for ``v2.0.0`` breaking "
"changes. This will be the last non-patch release within the ``v1.x`` stream."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:149
msgid ""
"Release ``v2.0.0-alpha1`` once all breaking changes have been completed. "
"We'll wait for users to report issues, bugs, and unexpected breakages at "
"this stage to ensure the release ``v2.0.0`` goes smoothly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:152
msgid "Development of remaining ``v2.x`` features starts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:153
msgid "Release ``v2.0.0`` which will be identical to ``v2.0.0-alpha1``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:154
msgid "Release ``v2.1.0`` with remaining ``v2.x`` features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:156
msgid "Deprecation warnings within ``v1.26.x`` will be opt-in by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:158
msgid "**More detailed Application Migration Guide coming soon.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:161
msgid "For Package Maintainers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:163
msgid ""
"Since this is the first major release in almost 9 years some users may be "
"caught off-guard by a new major release of urllib3. We're mitigating this by "
"trying to make ``v2.x`` API-compatible with ``v1.x``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:167
msgid ""
"If your application or library uses urllib3 and you'd like to be extra "
"cautious about not breaking your users, you can pin urllib3 like so until "
"you ensure compatibility with ``v2.x``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:171
msgid ""
"# 'install_requires' or 'requirements.txt'\n"
"\"urllib3>=1.25,<2\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-roadmap.rst:176
msgid ""
"We'd really appreciate testing compatibility and providing feedback on "
"``v2.0.0-alpha1`` once released."
msgstr ""
